### More detailed categories

The recoded data show that our clients seek for assistance in development of search strategies (where people haven’t started the search yet and asked for assistance) the most. This might be a good topic for crafting a KBA or instructional document. Our clients also appear to need some help in selection of databases (people do not know which databases to search in). We already have a resource on how to select a database [(KBA: Which databases should I search? A strategy for selecting appropriate sources)](https://new.library.cumc.columbia.edu/node/2257) which is a great resource to refer to. The trend of these two categories being most popular inquires persists from March, 2020. 

It is noteworthy that compared to March, 2020, inquiries regarding editing search strategies increased. This might suggest that some clients are repeaters or some more advanced clients started to use our services as they turned their focus to other scholarly pursuits that can be done remotely during the pandemic. It would be important to track and analyze the trends on this category, because if inquires shift from the development of search strategies to editing search strategies, this may be an indicator that our clients have enough confidence in the their ability to utilize our resources to start their own search (enabling self-learning) and our support can solidify and improve their search strategy to a higher level.  

```{r, echo=FALSE, warning=FALSE, message = FALSE}
#more detailed categories
infoApr20_CLN[, 31:115][is.na(infoApr20_CLN[, 31:115])] <- 0

infoApr20_CLN3 <- infoApr20_CLN
