### Online classes 

Five online classes were conducted in April, 2020. 

* Those are: 
    + Self-Editing Workshop (6 attendees)
    + Survival Skills Workshop (5 attendes)
    + Index Flex (3 attendees)
    + VP&S Mechanisms and Practice Seminar (~120 attendees)
    + So You Want to do a Systematic Review Class (1 attendee)
    
Total number clients served from the classes in April is about 135.  They are from various schools and affiliations, which includes but not limited to Mailman, SON, VP&S, and NYP. 

### Other

#### COVID-19

Among 64 tickets, 2 of them are COVID-19 related inquiries, 1 is likely to be COVID-19 related 

#### Forms 

We’ve started to use the new user inquiry form since early March, 2020. The majority of the web request come from the new form. However, unlike in the past, the number of inquiries via CUL form has increased. This might indicate that people are also finding the HSL services from the Morningside campus libraries. This may change  as we complete the transition to the new website and/or after we emerge from the pandemic. 

```{r, echo=FALSE, warning=FALSE, message=FALSE}
webReq <- infoApr20_CLN3 %>% filter(venue == "Website Request")

form <- table(webReq$form) %>% as.data.frame() %>% arrange(desc(Freq))
colnames(form) <- c("form", "count")

form$form <- as.character(form$form)
form$form <- toTitleCase(form$form)

formattable(form, 
            align = c("l", "r"))

```

Among the new forms, the majority of the tickets that are assigned to the informationists originated from the consult form, which suggest that this classification may be working and that  the information available from the new inquiry forms is playing an important role in helping the informationists to further unify how we are able to document user interactions. 

```{r, echo=FALSE, warning=FALSE, message=FALSE}
